  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Tip: This is to warm your tortillas later – alternatively, add them to a plate and pop in the microwave</p><p>Pat the <strong>basa fillets </strong>dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Cut the fillets at an angle, leaving 3 equally sized pieces</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1636731083498-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1636731083498-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1636731083498-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1636731083498-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1636731083498-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>soy sauce </strong>and <strong>cayenne pepper</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to a plate and mix it all together</p><p>Add the <strong>sliced basa </strong>to the spice plate and give everything a good mix up until fully coated, then set aside</p><p>Add 60g <span class=\"text-danger\">[120g]</span> <strong>flour</strong>, the <strong>white wine vinegar </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>to a separate bowl with 80ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[160ml] </span><strong>very cold water</strong> and mix thoroughly, then set aside for later – this is your <strong>batter</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1592916557132-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1592916557132-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1592916557132-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1592916557132-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1592916557132-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Top, tail and peel the <strong>mango<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong></p><p>Stand the <strong>mango<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> upright and very carefully slice the flesh away from the stone<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></p><p>Tip: If you feel resistance against your knife, it means you are hitting the stone</p><p>Dice the <strong>mango flesh</strong> finely, discarding the stone</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1592916565106-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1592916565106-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1592916565106-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1592916565106-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1592916565106-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Trim, then slice the <strong>spring onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s] </span></strong>finely</p><p>Cut the <strong>green chilli<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> in half lengthways, deseed (scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon) and chop finely</p><p>Dice the <strong>tomato<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong></p><p>Combine in a bowl the <strong>diced mango</strong>,<strong> chopped green chilli </strong>(not a fan of spice? Just add a little!),<strong> diced tomato </strong>and <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>spring onion </strong>with the juice of 1/2<strong> </strong><span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span> <strong>lime</strong>, a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> – this is your <strong>mango salsa</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
